                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-07-2019">July 2019</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-08-2019">August 2019</a></span> | <a href="/news-09-2019">September 2019</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Check the <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/seminars-hub">Seminars and Workshops Hub</a></strong> for schedule of upcoming events and to see notes from past events. August featured a seminar by A Random Day titled &quot;Writing Flash-Fiction SCP Articles&quot;.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Groups of Interest Power Rankings survey for 2019 has concluded! <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/group-of-interest-power-ranking-survey-results-2019">Check out the results here.</a></strong></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Wanderer's Library's <strong><a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/the-wanderer-s-station">new Sci-fi Contest</a></strong> has blasted off, with fabulous prizes for the daring winners.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>The following articles were selected for showcase by the <a href="/collaboration-contest">Collab-Con</a> Winners!</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>First Place Featured Articles</strong><br />
Chosen by Lt Flops and KindlyTurtleClem</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4175">SCP-4175</a> (&quot;Friends Made, and the Void&quot;) - <em>SCP-4175 is a Level-I Humanoid Apparition which can be viewed in the reflection of a bathroom vanity mirror.</em> Written by Nagiros</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4497">SCP-4497</a> (&quot;Whose Cuisine Reigns Supreme?!&quot;) - <em>SCP-4497 is a metaphysical mantle which imparts supernatural knowledge and skill within the domain of culinary arts.</em> Written by ManyMeats</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Second Place Featured Articles</strong><br />
Chosen by not_a_seagull and Mew-ltiverse</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4846">SCP-4846</a> (&quot;Friendly Fossils&quot;) - <em>SCP-4846 refers to a collection of anomalous fossils, with each instance possessing unique autonomous movement and interactive capabilities.</em> Written by Mew-ltiverse and Zyn</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3733">SCP-3733</a> (&quot;Everybody Else&quot;) - <em>The infection caused by SCP-3733 activates several typically inactive areas of the brain, resulting in the ability to act and reason outside of one's experiences and personality.</em> Written by not_a_seagull</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Third Place Featured Articles</strong><br />
Chosen by Uncle Nicolini and ihp</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/nicos-stupid-proposal">Uncle Nicolini's Proposal... Maybe.</a> - <em>Summer-Man: Just focus on punching the shark.</em> Written by Uncle Nicolini</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4918">SCP-4918</a> (&quot;Bergentruckung&quot;) - <em>SCP-4918 refers to several humanoid individuals possessing anomalous properties which first became active during the First World War.</em> Written by ihp</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4597">SCP-4597</a> (&quot;Thick-Skinned Man&quot;) - <em>SCP-4597's skin possesses accelerated, if flawed, regenerative properties.</em> Written by Weryllium, selected by <em>AKFrost</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4853">SCP-4853</a> (&quot;&amp;SCP-4853&quot;) - <em>Other references to SCP-4853 may exist only in this document, and may not exceed ten instances.</em> Written by aismallard, selected by <em>tupacofficial</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4954">SCP-4954</a> (&quot;Long Live the Tinsmith!&quot;) - <em>When worn by a human being, SCP-3881 will immediately transport the wearer to an unknown location.</em> Written by Nameless Mediocre, selected by <em>Gee0765</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4279">SCP-4279</a> (&quot;A Toast to my Finished Thesis&quot;) - <em>SCP-4279 uses electrical power to generate and assemble matter into theoretically any molecular or atomic form…</em> Written by Nameless Mediocre, selected by <em>Ayers</em></li>
</ul>
