<hr />
<p>You will notice little '📈' emojis beside some articles. That denotes SCP articles which were under 30 and tales which were under 20 when this edition of site news was posted. Give them a little love! Speaking from personal experience, the most frustrating thing that can happen to an article is not deletion, but stagnating below 20 without any comments. So try to read, vote, and comment on these articles! They're often hidden gems :)</p>
<h3 id="toc0"><span>Week of August 1st:</span></h3>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4938">SCP-4938</a> (&quot;Sweat of the Sun&quot;) - You probably believe it was lava, right ? Harvested (with some burns) by T Rutherford.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4468">SCP-4468</a> (&quot;Take-a-Wish&quot;) - Best hug ever. Written by DarkStuff.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4452">SCP-4452</a> (&quot;Submitted to the Ethics Committee for review&quot;) - Final request pending. Yep, still. It must have been, what, two years ? Waited by LiterallyMechanical.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4790">SCP-4790</a> (&quot;Do not go gentle into that good night.&quot;) - The stars are out, tonight. Written by Lt Flops.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4831">SCP-4831</a> (&quot;There Are Innocent People on Death Row&quot;) - Good day to die. Even if it's in the bathroom. Or in the toilet, like Elvis. Written by Westrin.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-4939">SCP-4939</a> (&quot;The Man on the Moon&quot;) - Oh, no, nevermind, they're still shining. Written by Mew-ltiverse.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-4351">SCP-4351</a> (&quot;Home&quot;) - <em>&quot;Totally not a documentary by Yann-Arthus Bertrand.&quot;</em> Purchased by TheSomnambulist.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-4462">SCP-4462</a> (&quot;Fan Death&quot;) - Causing death is the most sincere form of flattery. Written by GerrymanderBassist.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4215">SCP-4215</a> (&quot;The Inkredible 51st Squiddy Squaddy&quot;) - &quot;Your most favorite defence squids !&quot; Written by Popsioak.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4156">SCP-4156</a> (&quot;Last Bastion&quot;) - Exactly as stated. Defended by Tanhony.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-055-j">SCP-055-J</a> (&quot;Who Knows?&quot;) - It seems that beyond Josh Homme, no one knows. Written by Penton.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-4189">SCP-4189</a> (&quot;Vengeful Assimilation Coral&quot;) - Yep, they're definitely not happy with the actual condition of the Great Barrier. Written by Weryllium.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4971">SCP-4971</a> (&quot;Rituals&quot;) - Rituals, surprisingly, didn't became a has-been thing. Written by djkaktus.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4162">SCP-4162</a> (&quot;An Egg That Kills You For No Reason&quot;) - I told you that they were bandits, but no one listened. Broked by Tanhony.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4419">SCP-4419</a> (&quot;The Butcher's Chariot&quot;) - &quot;<em>If you see any person who need body modifications, call 911.</em>&quot; Written by Tanhony.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-4847">SCP-4847</a> (&quot;Akanastra&quot;) - <em>[INSERT JOKE ABOUT OLD MESOPOTAMIAN CITIES OR SAMSARA HERE]</em> Written by Dr Bjonk.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4698">SCP-4698</a> (&quot;Heir To Cernunnos&quot;) - &quot;<em>Today was shot to shit, to be frank.</em>&quot; Written by AbsentmindedNihilist.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4183">SCP-4183</a> (&quot;Automatic Containement Procedures&quot;) - Now, all is automatic ! Except writing all the blurbs for the Site News and I don't know why, damnit. Programmed by Tanhony.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc2"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>📈 <a href="/sweet-cream-pancakes">Sweet Cream Pancakes</a> - &quot;<em>Sweet Cream Pancakes, meanwhile, only had one-star reviews online because reviewers couldn’t give it anything lower.</em>&quot; Written by wmaitla.</li>
<li><a href="/vivid-visions">Vivid Visions</a> - &quot;<em>Sorry for bothering you, but lately I've started to experience some problems with my mental health.</em>&quot; Written by AlanDaris.</li>
<li><a href="/how-is-your-name">How Is Your Name?</a> - &quot;<em>Before we start, I need you to answer a very important question; am I a cartoon ?</em>&quot; Part of the <a href="/all-that-glisters">All That Glisters</a> series. Written by DrChandra.</li>
<li><a href="/shiny-gold-foil">Shiny Gold Foil</a> - &quot;<em>She was unshakable. Unflappable. No impossible case could stump her.</em>&quot; Written by Raddagher.</li>
<li><a href="/mister-nobody">Mister Nobody</a> - &quot;<em>Greetings, Arthur Barnes. You will be meeting with me soon. Nobody.</em>&quot; Written by gee0765.</li>
<li>📈 <a class="newpage" href="/the-chronicles-of-a-johnathan-sole-perem-chapter-i-enter-the">The Chronicles of a Johnathan Sole Perem Chapter I: Enter The Spoiled Tick</a> - &quot;<em>I would like to let you know, for the past month, someone has been summoning and sending brainless mongrels here non stop !</em>&quot; Written by RadioactiveRADS.</li>
<li><a href="/abwesenheit">Abwesenheit</a> - &quot;<em>Hellmuth's work is characterized by sparse structure, emotional isolation, fascination with negative space, no dialogue, and single extraordinarily long takes.</em>&quot; Written by The Great Hippo.</li>
<li><a href="/tower-b">Tower-B</a> - &quot;<em>Deep-sea sat-divers are kind of like celebrities. There aren't a lot of them — just a couple hundred in the whole wide world.</em>&quot; Written by The Great Hippo.</li>
<li><a href="/a-hero-i-would-be">A Hero I Would Be!</a> - &quot;<em>Wait, it feels like I've… Oh ! You're one of those plastics people, right ? What, did Mr. Albany's lycanthropy act up again ?</em>&quot; Part of <a href="/the-s-c-plastics-hub">S&amp;C Plastiques</a> canon. Written by Ellie3.</li>
<li><a href="/skunk-ape">Skunk Ape</a> - &quot;<em>Life is different when you've been widowed.</em>&quot; Written by Roget.</li>
<li><a href="/sunday-dinner">Straight to VHS: Sunday Dinner</a> - &quot;<em>We soothe our conscience by telling ourselves it's just a movie — all while a tiny voice teases and thrills us with just a whisper : but what if it's not ?</em>&quot; Written by The Great Hippo.</li>
<li><a href="/scared-stiff">Scared Stiff</a> - &quot;<em>If you were like me as a kid, you probably weren't interested in reading anything. Except, of course, the &quot;Scared Stiff&quot; series.</em>&quot; Written by Oboebandgeek99.</li>
<li><a href="/gluttony-is-impossible">Gluttony Is Impossible</a> - &quot;<em>Last year, Thailand was affected by the most devastating earthquake in the area of the last hundred years. Despite the United Nation's best efforts to feed the victims of this catastrophe, they only have so many resources.</em>&quot; Part of the <a href="/end-of-death-hub">End of Death</a> canon. Written by Uncle Nicolini.</li>
<li><a href="/piercing-the-veil">Masquerade's End</a> - &quot;<em>i dont know whats scarier, whats happening or the fact that the scp foundation thinks a lab in a lab coat is gonna make us feel better</em>&quot; Part of the <a href="/broken-masquerade-hub">Broken Masquerade</a> canon. Written by Uncle Nicolini.</li>
<li>📈 <a class="newpage" href="/the-carcosa-veldt-congregation">The Carcosa Veldt Congregation</a> - &quot;<em>There is a humanoid resembling an anthropomorphic coyote within the cordon around Carcosa and it distracted me,&quot; I announced, &quot;It is wearing a leather jacket and a crucifix and has demonstrated limited ontokinetic abilities.&quot;</em>&quot; Written by Cregan Stark.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc3"><span>GoI Formats</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/peligro-igniciervos">Danger: Incinideer!</a> - [Wilson's Wildlife Solutions] &quot;<em>Our family expands into Latin America!</em>&quot; Written by INT_Translator.</li>
<li><a href="/the-hanged-king-s-tragedy">The Hanged King's Tragedy</a> - [The Black Queen] &quot;<em>⁂ Erasmus was banished</em>&quot; Written by Oboebandgeek99.</li>
<li><a href="/adoption-poster-darius">Adoption Poster: Darius!</a> - [Wilson's Wildlife Solutions] &quot;<em>Hey, Esther. It's been a while. How is Darius?</em>&quot; Written by Uncle Nicolini.</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<h3 id="toc4"><span>Week of August 8th:</span></h3>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-577">SCP-577</a> (&quot;All Alone In The Moonlight&quot;) - Hey, was this really MY cat ? Originally written by Dr Kondraki, rewritten by MayD.</li>
<li>📈 <a href="/scp-es-105">SCP-ES-105</a> (&quot;Stargazing the Other Stars&quot;) - I think that this month, there's some bad blood between us and the stars. Or a sort of obsession. I don't know. Written by INT_Translator.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4495">SCP-4495</a> (&quot;A God for Pigs&quot;) - &quot;<em>All the Skippers are all lined up. I give you all that you want. Take my description and peel it back. Now, doesn't it make you feel better ?</em>&quot; Written by UraniumEmpire.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4254">SCP-4254</a> (&quot;Elvis ?&quot;) - That's with this type of rumors that you can easily say &quot;<em>Rock isn't dead</em>&quot;. Composed and performed by Tanhony.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4484">SCP-4484</a> (&quot;StreamSavers&quot;) - &quot;Why this site is only focused on dogs ? We all know that cats are much better.&quot; Adopted by Roget.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4972">SCP-4972</a> (&quot;Something is Wrong&quot;) - As usual. Written by Tanhony.</li>
